      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIOGO KEEPING (5) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 3.5 lengths win at Murray Bridge in a handy 22.19. Has a tricky draw to overcome but goes well over this trip. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. CARRY ON KIM (1) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 6 lengths back in second (22.63) at this track in a OPEN over 400m. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from six attempts. Winning chance. BRINDLE BENNY (2) ran the fastest on the card last time scoring by 5 lengths (19.51) at Angle Park. Speedy runner and should be in the action early from an inside box. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. IMAGINE THE FUN (8) has strong credentials over this journey.",
